> Béarnaise is one of the most elegant toppings you can put on a steak—the French sauce sings with fragrant tarragon and a splash of white wine vinegar. We've adapted it slightly to make it lighter and brighter, so that it bathes this rib-eye steak in flavors that feel vibrant without being heavy. With asparagus and crispy roasted spuds on the side, it feels like a luxuriant upgrade to classic meat and potatoes.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. (TIP: Quarter any large ones so they cook evenly.) Strip and finely chop enough @rosemary{¼%ounce} from stems to give you 1 TBSP. Toss potatoes, rosemary, and a drizzle of oil on a #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast potatoes in oven until browned, about ~{25%minutes} total (we'll add more to the sheet after ~{10%minutes}). Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Pick and roughly chop enough @tarragon{¼%ounce} leaves from stems to give you 1 TBSP. Trim woody bottom ends from @asparagus{8%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @rib-eye steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest. Reduce heat to medium low.

After potatoes have roasted for 10 minutes, remove from oven and toss, pushing toward one side of baking sheet. Add asparagus to other side of sheet, toss with a drizzle of oil, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return sheet to oven and continue roasting until asparagus is tender and lightly browned and potatoes are done, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Add shallot to #pan{} used for steak. Cook, tossing, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} and scrape up any browned bits on bottom. Add chopped tarragon. Cook until vinegar evaporates, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @water{½%cup} and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in @butter{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice steak against the grain. Divide potatoes, asparagus, and steak between plates. Spoon sauce over steak and serve.